.TH timew-split 1 "${PACKAGE_DATE}" "${PACKAGE_STRING}" "User Manuals"
.
.SH NAME
timew-split \- split intervals
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B timew split
.I <id>
.B ...
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
Ð…plits an interval into two equally sized adjacent intervals, having the same tags.
Using the 'summary' command, and specifying the ':ids' hint shows interval IDs.
Using the right ID, you can identify an interval to split.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
For example, show the IDs:
.RS
$ timew summary :week :ids
.RE
Then having selected '@2' as the interval you wish to split:
.RS
$ timew split @2
.RE
.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR timew-join (1),
.BR timew-lengthen (1),
.BR timew-shorten (1)